cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.PE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses wireless energy harvesting sensor networks, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes a system where mobile actors move along pre-decided patterns, which can be considered as a multi-agent system. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the impact of energy transfer on the overall lifetime of the mobile sensor-actor networks, which can be considered as a control problem. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper proposes mobility models for the mobile actors, which can be related to robotics. 
5. cs.PE (Performance) - The paper evaluates the performance of the proposed system through simulation-based studies, which can be considered as a performance evaluation.
